# Next.js App Router

This project uses Next.js 16 with the App Router (`src/app/`). Read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` before changing routing, data fetching, or caching APIs — this version has breaking changes from older Next.js.

## Defaults

- Prefer Server Components; add `"use client"` only for browser APIs, event handlers, or client hooks.
- Use `layout.tsx` for shared shell, `page.tsx` for route UI, and `loading.tsx` / `error.tsx` when those states matter.
- Use `route.ts` handlers for API endpoints when needed (not required for current movie data flow).
- Export `metadata` or `generateMetadata` from layouts/pages for SEO.

## Async route props (Next.js 15+)

`searchParams`, `params`, and `headers()` are async. Await them in Server Components:

```tsx
interface HomeProps {
  searchParams: Promise<{ q?: string }>;
}

export default async function Home({ searchParams }: HomeProps) {
  const { q } = await searchParams;
}
```

## Data fetching

- Fetch MongoDB data in Server Components or `src/lib/` modules — not in Client Components.
- Wrap slow or search-driven UI in `<Suspense>` with a meaningful fallback.
- Handle errors in the page and surface a user-facing message instead of throwing uncaught errors.

## Images and assets

- Use `next/image` for posters and remote images; keep `alt` text descriptive.
- Put static assets in `public/`.

## File conventions

Follow Next.js special filenames: `page.tsx`, `layout.tsx`, `loading.tsx`, `error.tsx`, `not-found.tsx`, `route.ts`.
